      "writtenOn": "2019-03-28T19:08:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I can revert all of the Skia changes if you\u0027d prefer.  This was specifically requested by the ANGLE team.\n\nTo be clear, we won\u0027t upload a new CL during the day, but if there are new commits while we\u0027re still in the window, we will upload CLs.  I deliberately excluded skcms since I figured we wanted those commits to roll ASAP.  I didn\u0027t think we were super worried about a day or two delay for Swiftshader or ANGLE, but I could be wrong.  Personally, I thought there were an excess of rolls from those two rollers throughout the day, so it seemed better to condense to a single nightly roll.  As you say, a failing roll will continue to fail until the sheriff arrives.  That seems like desirable behavior, compared to failing once and then being silent all day.",
